On Apr 5, 2004, at 3:39 PM, Mike Soultanian wrote:

> Exhaust wrapping is fiberglass-mesh webbing, approximately 3 
> millimeters thick, and about 6 centimeters wide. It is applied by 
> moistening the mesh, then wrapping the exhaust spiral fashion. The 
> webbing hardens into a chrysalis around the pipes.

I've thought about adding such to my Bus.  But I've heard folks talk 
about how the metal underneath the wrap super-heats and disintegrates.  
'76 California exhaust parts are already hard enough to find... I'm not 
sure I'm interested in destroying the perfectly serviceable parts that 
I have :-)

